You MUST install native connector for this extension to work.

For Arch Linux there is a PKGBUILD available in the AUR: https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/chrome-gnome-shell-git

For Debian Linux there is package available in Sid and Stretch: https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/chrome-gnome-shell

For Fedora Linux there is package available in Copr: https://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/region51/chrome-gnome-shell

In Gentoo Linux you can install connector with command:
emerge gnome-extra/chrome-gnome-shell

For Ubuntu Linux you can install connector with command:
sudo apt install chrome-gnome-shell

You also can install connector manually. See https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/GnomeShellIntegrationForChrome/Installation for install instructions.
